CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 18, 1953, pg. 6, reads: "Youth Conference Planners - These young people, members of various agencies, are planning a vocational conference to be held in May at the Irene Kaufmann Settlement. They are, seated: Yvonne Greene, Gwendolyn Thompkins, Gwendolyn Wilmer, James Wilmer, chairman of the planning committee; Evelyn Warfield, assistant secretary, and Gladys Miller, secretary. Standing: Vivian Gravis, Joseph Lamar, Alice Platt, Rebecca Solomon, Howard Morris and Letitio [Letitia] Averyth. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, standing from left: Vivian Gravis, Joseph Lamar, Alice Platt, Rebecca Solomon, Howard Morris, Letitia Averyth; seated: Yvonne Greene, Gwendolyn Thompkins, Gwendolyn Wilmer, James Wilmer, Evelyn Warfield, and Gladys Miller, gathered around round table to plan vocational youth conference at the Irene Kaufmann Settlement
